message.content:
For some reason the orderlies had forgotten to switch on the lights; there were no colour-
physical features were distinguishable solely by gradients of silvery greyness. Even the snow-
capped summit of Mont Blanc, seven miles below, was not recognisable among the host of lower peaks. The screen of the air-to-air radar glowed, occasionally minute spots flickered across its surface, but there were no permanent image.
